<TEXT>
west germany said friday it would 
guarantee a bank credit of about 31 billion for the soviet union 
to help president mikhail s gorbachev reform his countrys ailing 
economy 
chief government spokesman hans klein said the 12year bank 
credit marks the start of a west german initiative to get 
largescale international support for the soviet union 
in a related development west german chancellor helmut kohl and 
french president francois mitterrand called friday for quick 
economic help to support soviet reforms and the rebuilding of 
eastern europe 
the two leaders held more than two hours of private talks on a 
boat on the rhine river near of assmannshausen west of wiesbaden 
as part of their regular germanfrench consultations 
the 5 billion deutsche mark bank credit worth nearly 31 
billion was negotiated by the deutsche bank and the dresdner bank 
with the foreign trade bank in the soviet union 
the credit aims to help the soviet union make the transition 
from a centrally planned economy to a market economy an effort 
that is similar to reform plans in other east bloc countries 
the announcement was made as foreign ministers from the two 
germanys and the four victorious world war ii allies the united 
states soviet union britain and france began two days of talks 
in berlin on resolving differences over german unification 
west germany has indicated its willingness to broaden economic 
cooperation with the soviet union as part of shaping future 
relations with a united germany bonn would also like to see moscow 
drop its bitter objections to membership in the north atlantic 
treaty organization for a unified germany 
the soviet union also stands to lose one of its key economic 
partners as east germany unites with west germany many of the east 
german firms with which the soviet union trades are likely to go 
bankrupt once the two germanys merge their currencies on july 2 
others that survive will have their products priced in the new 
expensive marks 
kohl said his talks with mitterrand concerned preparations for 
the upcoming european economic community summit in dublin the nato 
summit in london and the world economic summit in houston 
he said they were convinced that decisions would be reached in 
dublin and houston about how the reform processes in eastern 
europe and especially in the soviet union could be supported but 
it was not yet settled how much financial help they were talking 
about 
the european economic community must understand the importance 
of giving help toward selfhelp because the politics of 
perestroika helps us all kohl said 
we have very little time he added 
mitterrand concurred saying the matter is really urgent 
</TEXT>
