<TEXT>
india will shut gasoline stations on 
sundays and limit their business hours during the week because it 
doesnt have enough money to import more oil officials say 
ms gurupadaswamy the petroleum and natural gas minister 
announced steps beginning this weekend that he said will save 26 
million tons of petroleum products this year a savings of 500 
million 
he ordered the sale of gasoline and diesel to be restricted to 
between 7 am and 7 pm as well as closure on sundays 
gas station operators and consumers said friday the plan wont 
work because people will just buy more gas during the remaining 
business hours 
there will be more crowds lots of frayed tempers fights 
said rc pillai a salesman at a gas station 
according to government estimates india will have to import 246 
million tons of crude oil and petroleum products this year and pay 
35 billion indias foreign debt is about 60 billion 
