completed by 1995 
halprins design calls for long sequences of paved walkways and 
shaded exterior rooms containing sculptures and inscriptions 
dealing with various aspects of roosevelts four terms as 
president from the great depression in the early 1930s through 
world war ii 
roosevelt died of a cerebral hemorrhage in warm springs ga on 
april 12 1945 less than a month before nazi germany surrendered 
to the western allies and the soviet union 
