roughhewn granite walls fountains pools and waterfalls on a site 
in west potomac park within sight of the potomac river close to 
the southeastern edge of the tidal basin about 400 yards west of 
the jefferson memorial 
left undecided is the fate of the only existing roosevelt 
memorial a simple block of white stone with plaque in a small 
triangular park in front of the national archives building on 
pennsylvania avenue 
efforts to build a suitable memorial to the 32nd president date 
to the mid1950s two previous designs for abstract monuments were 
withdrawn in the 1960s after much criticism one was denounced as 
instant stonehenge and the project languished for lack of 
money 
