<TEXT>
the red double doors of no 6 fuqiang lane are 
closed tight and knots of police eye those who pass by the 
reported home of chinas most famous political prisoner former 
communist party chief zhao ziyang 
i cant talk here said one chinese woman glancing 
nervously at the walled compound where zhao and his family are said 
to reside 
zhao chinas former premier and the man once mentioned as the 
leading contender to replace deng xiaoping as chinas senior 
leader has not been seen for 13 months 
sunday marks one year since the party central committee met to 
purge the reformminded zhao of all party posts accusing him of 
splitting the party and supporting the turmoil he was 
replaced byshanghai bureaucrat jiang zemin a political hardliner 
the turmoil referred to the studentled prodemocracy 
movement that the military crushed june 4 1989 zhao opposed the 
military intervention but was overruled by premier li peng and 
other conservatives who used the dispute to drive zhao and his 
supporters from power 
zhaos last public appearance was on may 19 1989 when he had a 
tearful meeting with student hunger strikers on tiananmen square 
the next day li declared martial law in beijing 
since then his only known contact with the world came recently 
when former german chancellor helmut schmidt said zhao responded to 
a personal letter 
his comfortable prison on fuqiang lane was once the home of hu 
yaobang his predecessor as party chief who was also purged in 
january 1987 for showing sympathy to prodemocracy student 
demonstrations 
hus death in april 1989 led to the mass rallies that propelled 
the spring movement for democratic reforms 
in the weeks after zhaos purge party leaders hinted strongly 
that zhao would face criminal charges for supporting the democracy 
movement or counterrevolutionary rebellion members of his 
family were also said to be under investigation for corruption 
zhao was maligned in the official press as a man who had 
vilified and repudiated the fine traditions of the party 
zhao now 70 may have avoided a trial so far because he has 
long been a favorite of deng for nearly a decade zhao 
administered dengs marketoriented reforms which brought new 
levels of prosperity to china 
the conservatives may be treading cautiously because party 
reformers while in retreat the past year are still a popular and 
formidable force particularly in areas of the country that have 
benefited from the reforms 
zhao may have made some mistakes but we shouldnt blame him 
for everything guo shuyan governor of the central hubei 
province said in a recent interview 
unable to reach a consensus the party has left zhao in limbo 
his old rival li peng said in april that zhao was a free man 
who was still a member of the communist party and enjoyed quite 
good living conditions 
li said zhao reported to have suffered from heart trouble late 
last year was in good health and he joked that zhao received a 
bigger salary than he did 
according to hong kong news reports zhao was summoned before 
members of the party politburo in march and accused of seriously 
violating party discipline but zhao reportedly refused to admit 
any guilt 
overt public criticism of zhao has largely abated 
with the investigation into his case apparently going nowhere 
the man still officially referred to as comrade faces an 
indefinite period of house arrest 
some talk wistfully of a comeback when political fortunes 
change after all deng was 74 when he made his last return to 
power in 1979 
but china watchers say zhao has no political future unless 
chinas leadership acknowledges it was wrong in its bloody 
suppression of the tiananmen demonstrators an unlikely prospect 
soon 
the government has also undermined zhaos power base by 
arresting some allies removing others from provincial governments 
and breaking up political institutes linked to him 
deng has proclaimed that new party leader jiang is now the 
core of the leadership 
jiang has learned a lesson from dengs former proteges hu and 
zhao he has carefully toed the rigid line set down by the aging 
leaders in their own walled compound not far from fuqiang lane 
