<TEXT>
strong aftershocks struck northern iran 
before dawn today terrifying survivors of an earthquake two days 
earlier that some officials say killed 40000 people and injured 
100000 
foreign emergency aid poured into iran but the islamic 
government was balking at allowing international medical and rescue 
personnel into the affected region on the caspian sea about 125 
miles northwest of tehran 
the task of rescuers grew grimmer today as hopes faded for 
finding anyone else alive in the rubble of dozens of towns and 
villages in the devastated provinces of gilan and zanjan 
attention also turned to finding shelter for an estimated 
400000 people left homeless by the disaster 
there were conflicting death tolls hossein zeineddin second 
secretary with irans un mission in new york said late friday 
that according to the latest estimates from the region at least 
40000 people were killed and 100000 were injured 
the official islamic republic news agency reported 28950 people 
killed 25241 in gilan province and 3709 in zanjan province 
the toll surpassed that of the quake that killed 25000 people 
in nearby soviet armenia in december 1988 and a quake in iran in 
1978 that also killed 25000 
it was the worst quake since july 28 1976 when an estimated 
200000 people were killed in china by a quake measuring 78 to 82 
on the richter scale 
more than 200 aftershocks have hit since thursdays predawn 
earthquake which registered at least 73 on the richter scale 
irna monitored in cyprus said one aftershock jolted the 
northern provincial capital of rasht early today making 
panicstricken residents take to the streets three hours later 
another shock measuring 4 on the richter scale hit the town of 
roodbar in the heart of the quake zone where workers were pulling 
bodies from the rubble it said 
irna said friday that 6000 survivors had been rescued but by 
today workers were mainly finding the dead 
rescue workers are becoming less optimistic irna said late 
friday the number of those taken out alive has dropped sharply 
in tehran the capital the government ordered that 20 percent 
of all beds in private hospitals be set aside for quake victims 
an official announcement said six major airports have been 
designated as centers for the shipment of supplies to the quake 
area in northern iran and the transfer of injured to hospitals out 
of the area 
the government appealed for international help and nations all 
around the world responded with offers of aid including the 
united states britain and israel all regarded by tehran as 
enemies 
iran reportedly said it would accept assistance from all 
countries except israel and south africa 
the united states and iran have not had diplomatic ties since 
the 1979 seizure of hostages at the us embassy in tehran britain 
and iran severed diplomatic relations in march 1989 after the late 
ayatollah ruhollah khomeini ordered moslems to kill british author 
salman rushdie for his novel the satanic verses 
the european community promised to donate 24 million japan 
15 million and sweden 820000 other countries including 
jordan and china planned to ship tons of supplies 
messages of condolence also continued to arrive the latest from 
libya and saudi arabia which has accused iran of terrorism and 
broke ties in april 1988 
while the iranians welcomed emergency supplies and cash 
donations the government discouraged the presence of foreign 
rescue workers and medical personnel however some international 
teams including a group of french doctors had already arrived 
today 
the british broadcasting corp quoted a briton who arrived with 
a british aid shipment as saying the iranians indicated they did 
not want foreigners operating in the quake area but he said they 
were allowing them to set up medical treatment units and 
supplydistribution points in tehran 
in the crucial hours after the quake landslides blocked 
rescuers routes on the ground and bad weather hampered airborne 
efforts 
if you had come earlier you could have saved my 
daughterinlaw i was talking to her until a few hours ago irna 
quoted an elderly survivor as telling rescuers in the village of 
jamalabad in zanjan province 
iranian television monitored in cyprus showed masked rescuers 
in white aprons pulled dustcovered bodies from under concrete 
slabs corpses were laid on blocks of ice in open trucks 
the television showed scenes of devastation including the 
remains of an entire row of hillside village houses that collapsed 
and slid down the hill 
president hashemi rafsanjani flew to the village of roodbar in 
the heart of the affected region friday and told iranian television 
that everyone is helping but with a calamity this disastrous 
nothing could be enough 
farhad shad a spokesman for the geophysics center at tehran 
university told irna that 140 aftershocks were registered after 
the killer earthquake which measured 73 to 77 on the richter 
scale according to geological stations in tehran edinburgh 
scotland and golden colo 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph every increase of one number means that the ground 
motion is 10 times greater a quake of magnitude 7 is considered a 
major earthquake 
