also seemed more human partly because of a frailty from age 
medical problems jet lag and 27 years in prison 
the 71yearold mandelas arrival from canada was delayed for 
several hours by his need to rest and soon organizers were lopping 
some events from his schedule and curtailing others organizer 
roger wilkins said wednesday night mandela had reached the 
limit 
columnist murray kempton wrote that mandelas tired face evoked 
a spirit that has endured much and must endure much to come 
but mandela kept undercutting concerns about his health with 
signs of vitality 
an hour after he had remained seated while speaking to religious 
leaders at riverside church doctors orders he apologized he 
stepped confidently up the altar steps looking like the former 
boxer and guerrilla whose daily exercise regimen got him through 
the prison years 
he rose early thursday morning at the mayors house and went for 
a stroll along the east river he was as curious as any tourist 
asking about the pollution in the river the distance between 
washington and new york he told reporters he felt on top of the 
world 
he also had time for children the last person koppel called on 
