prime minister brian mulroney told canadians 
today he is deeply disappointed by the failure of a 
constitutional amendment that would have accorded special status to 
frenchspeaking quebec 
we have missed the opportunity to turn the page and start a 
new chapter in constitutional history mulroney said in a 
nationwide television broadcast 
but he reached out to the people of quebec saying that quebec 
emerged from these negotiations with its dignity and its principles 
intact 
