a communications satellite similar 
to one that ended up stranded in a uselessly low orbit three months 
ago was launched to its proper altitude saturday officials said 
the intelsat vi satellite rode into orbit on a titan 3 unmanned 
rocket which lifted off on time from cape canaveral air force 
station it was the same kind of rocket that had left the earlier 
intelsat vi satellite stranded 
the satellite separated from the rocket 25 minutes after 
liftoff bringing cheers and applause in the mission control room 
a rocket wiring problem prevented separation after the march 14 
launch 
were all very anxious to see this mission totally successful 
and were certainly expecting it to be that way said edward m 
browne president of martin marietta commercial titan inc when 
that thing went off separation we were all very happy and we 
naturally let our emotions show that 
a little more than an hour after liftoff an onboard motor 
boosted the satellite to an elliptical orbit 22300 miles above 
earth a series of firings over the next several days will put the 
spacecraft in a circular stationary orbit 
browne said the 270 million launch which includes the cost of 
the 150 million satellite was super totally flawless 
the stranded spacecraft is orbiting about 345 miles above earth 
22000 miles lower than intended that satellite and the one 
launched saturday were not insured 
intelsats board of governors agreed earlier this month to pay 
nasa 90 million for a shuttle rescue mission in which 
spacewalking astronauts will attach a motor to the stranded 
satellite to boost it up to its proper orbit that mission is 
scheduled for 1992 
the satellite deployed saturday joins 14 other intelsat 
spacecraft in orbit once operational in early september the 
40footlong 2ton satellite will be capable of relaying the 
transmissions of three tv channels and up to 120000 telephone 
calls simultaneously 
intelsat a washingtonbased consortium of 119 countries plans 
to send up its next two intelsat vi satellites on the european 
space agencys ariane rocket both launches are scheduled for next 
year 
the next commercial titan launch with nasas mars observer 
spacecraft is set for 1992 
