asian countries have given the united states until july 1 to 
arrange new options for people screened out as ineligible for 
resettlement 
the asian nations have been joined by britain which has urged 
the united states to drop its objections to forced repatriation or 
accept thousands of boat people who do not qualify as political 
refugees the british colony of hong kong has a large community of 
vietnamese refugees 
immigrants deemed to be fleeing poverty rather than political 
repression are not granted refugee status 
