president mikhail s gorbachev promised saturday 
he would hold the splintering communist party together and remain 
its leader despite the growing division between conservatives and 
reformers 
the pledge came at the communist party congress in the biggest 
soviet republic which elected as its leader a hardliner who is 
unacceptable to many reformist communists 
