<TEXT>
strong aftershocks sent panicked residents 
rushing into the streets of northern iran on saturday and mass 
graves were dug for victims of an earthquake that some official 
reports say killed at least 40000 people 
efforts continued to rescue people trapped under piles of rubble 
in the mountainous areas of irans northwestern gilan and zamjan 
provinces that were devastated in thursdays quake 
today we found eight people alive but they will probably be 
the last we uncover said nassir zadeh an officer of the 
revolutionary guard helping search and rescue operations in the 
flattened city of rudbar about 140 miles northwest of tehran 
the official islamic republic news agency reported that with 
the lapse of time hope was fading that more survivors could be 
found alive under the rubble thursdays quake destroyed dozens of 
towns and villages caspian sea region 
journalists flying over the area saw horrific scenes of 
devastation in villages where thousands of mud brick and concrete 
homes were reduced to rubble no estimates of casualties were yet 
available from remote regions 
numerous mountain villages remained cut off because landslides 
blocked roads 
in rudbar dozens of iranian military helicopters flew supplies 
into makeshift airstrips on a small island in the river that flows 
through this agricultural center that once numbered 180000 people 
the twolane roads leading to rudbar and neighboring manjil were 
clogged with rubble from buildings and huge boulders dislodged from 
the surrounding hills 
milelong columns of buses ambulances and flatbed trucks 
carrying bulldozers cranes and other equipment had to wait for 
hours to reach their destinations 
foreign relief teams and supplies began arriving in the region 
as the world responded to the disaster 
there were conflicting death tolls a national radio broadcast 
said more than 40000 people were feared dead and 100000 were 
injured irna reported about 29000 people killed 
in rudbar earthquake victims were buried in mass graves 
without counting the bodies because of the heavy death toll 
irna said the quake destroyed the only hospital there 
the quake destroyed or damaged about 95 percent of the citys 
buildings and residents were reduced to living in thousands of 
tents pitched near the roads as temperatures soared to 105 degrees 
twelve members of my family died when our house collapsed 
said a weeping woman sitting in front of a tent pitched next to 
the remains of her home 
amrola mosadei a carpenter said i tried to grab my 
daughters arm when the house started swaying but then she was 
gone and the roof collapsed 
more than 200 aftershocks have hit the region the biggest 
registering 42 on the richter scale and rocking the tarome olia 
region about 125 miles northwest of tehran irna said thursdays 
quake was at least 73 on the richter scale 
another large shock jolted the northern city of rasht early 
saturday making panicstricken residents take to the streets 
it said there was also a third powerful aftershock in the area 
aftershocks which continue in the mountainous regions are 
endangering the relief operation the news agency said 
the toll surpassed a quake that killed 25000 people in nearby 
soviet armenia in december 1988 and a quake in iran in 1978 that 
also killed 25000 
the quakes toll was the highest anywhere since july 28 1976 
when an estimated 200000 people were killed in china by a quake 
our people have learned to resist difficulties and consider 
the national disaster to be a divine test president hashemi 
rafsanjani told syrias foreign minister farouk alsharaa 
we have submitted ourselves to gods will 
state television monitored in cyprus showed injured people 
lying on the ground in long rows with health workers passing back 
and forth with medication as flies swarmed around 
army helicopters landed in a field and picked up the injured on 
stretchers while a woman in the traditional black chador carried a 
tiny child in a bundle of cloth 
the television showed numerous bodies wrapped in white shrouds 
grieving women wailed nearby dozens of other bodies many wrapped 
in carpets lay unclaimed beside a road 
a grayhaired man lifted chunks of concrete from a building with 
the help of younger men then burst into tears when a body was 
uncovered presumably a family member 
one shot from a helicopter showed a fissure in a plowed field 
that gaped open at least three yards at its widest point it was 
several yards deep and hundreds of yards long 
a 205member french relief team arrived in iran friday night 
and at least 200 relief workers from the soviet union also traveled 
to the region irna reported the official soviet news agency tass 
said an armenian team that rescued people in the 1988 armenian 
earthquake went to iran 
in soviet azerbaijan which borders iran and has strong ethnic 
ties with much of its population the president declared a day of 
mourning saturday and black flags flew across the republic tass 
said 
irans health department sent 100 teams into the area to prevent 
the outbreak of contagious diseases 
iran at odds with the united states since the 1979 seizure of 
hostages at the us embassy in tehran said it would welcome 
relief from the american red cross and other us humanitarian 
groups the two nations have no diplomatic ties 
we want to be helpful without regard for our political 
differences with iran said richard boucher deputy state 
department spokesman in washington 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
