god as in the priesthood 
ancient jewish law is uniformly against homosexuality the first 
reference in leviticus states that with a man shalt thou not 
lie as with a woman it is an abomination 
reform judaism is not strictly bound by ancient jewish law but 
allows for thousands of years of social change that have occurred 
since moses time it was the first branch of judaism to ordain 
women as rabbis in 1972 
