a rem is a standard measure of dose from powerful ionizing 
radiation like xrays or nuclear radioactivity doses often are 
expressed in millirem or thousandths of a rem a chest xray from 
an uptodate machine will expose the patient to about 20 millirems 
for longterm exposure of the general public the commission is 
maintaining its current recommendation of no more than 100 millirem 
per year on average but it is suggesting that the averaging period 
be five years instead of a lifetime 
