<TEXT>
try to remember 30 years ago when the 
fantasticks opened offbroadway and went on to make theater 
history as the worlds longestrunning musical 
now a new version of this simple parable about romantic 
illusions is about to begin a 40city national tour with a full 
orchestra a chorus and robert goulet starring as the narrator 
it was to have opened here at the 2741seat orpheum theatre 
monday night but slow ticket sales caused theater owners to cancel 
you need the bodies to make these things work orpheum 
manager fred krohn said every year at this time we seem to have 
a lull in sales krohn said none of the shows was more than half 
sold when the decision was made thursday to cancel the run 
michael sterling a publicist for the tour said the show will 
move to the state fair music hall in dallas its next scheduled 
stop and play from july 3july 15 the musical is part of a 
15week season there and tickets were sold as part of a package 
itll be a new discovery said lyricist tom jones who wrote 
the fantasticks with composer harvey schmidt in 1959 
i believe its going to be a revelation for people whove 
never seen it or even more so for people whove only seen it in an 
amateur production 
since opening at the 153seat sullivan street playhouse in 
greenwich village on may 3 1960 the fantasticks has run for 
more than 12500 performances 
in addition to being the worlds longestrunning musical and the 
longestrunning show in american theater history the 
fantasticks is the most frequently produced musical in the world 
a favorite college and amateur production the fantasticks has 
been staged more than 11000 times in the united states and more 
than 700 times in 68 other countries 
the musical best known for the song try to remember is 
based on an 1894 play les romanesque by edmond rostand the 
story is a reverse romeo and juliet in which parents invent a 
feud to bring their children together a boy and a girl find love 
at the end of act 1 then separate and become disillusioned before 
understanding each other at the end of act 2 
with its eightmember cast and sparse scenery the 
fantasticks usually is performed in an intimate setting with 
piano and harp accompaniment 
for the shows first national tour a 16piece orchestra and a 
sevenmember chorus with orchestrations by hollywood conductor jack 
elliott were added a new song was written and new sets and 
costumes were designed by the shows original designer ed 
wittstein 
the fantasticks originally cost 16500 to stage in 1960 
the cost of the 30th anniversary national tour is close to 1 
million 
jones believes the plays message wont be lost in a big 
production 
i feel it enhances the piece he said 
in 1987 the peking opera performed the fantasticks in a 
6000seat auditorium the next year jones and schmidt directed a 
production that toured japan in theaters of 1000 seats or more 
we found that in every instance the places where we expanded 
the musical not only didnt take away from the show but they 
helped it they clarified it and made it more fun jones said 
jones calls the fantasticks a celebration of the theater 
the musical borrows such devices as the oriental invisible propman 
stock comic figures from italian commedia del larte and a narrator 
from greek theater 
when you go to the theater you want to have an experience 
thats different from this experience of watching television or 
going to a film jones said 
universal themes in the fantasticks may account for its 
popularity he said it has to do with growing up with letting 
go of some romantic romanticism and settling for more everyday 
life its an attempt to celebrate young love and romanticize it 
and mock it at the same time 
goulet who debuted on broadway in 1960 as lancelot in 
camelot was the authors first choice to play the narrator el 
gallo in the tour 
hes very right for it first of all hes been signing and 
recording try to remember for 25 years or more jones said 
goulet has starred in traveling productions of on a clear day 
you can see forever carousel and south pacific 
its hard to find a star name who can actually deliver 
material like he can schmidt said 
as the narrator goulet portrays a matineeidol vision of what 
the girl and the boy believe a dashing hero should be for the role 
of el gallo jones said he wanted a bullfighter whos been gored 
and robert has been gored and hes experienced and hes been 
burned a little bit 
goulet sees the role as that of a combination swashbuckler poet 
and teacher 
i like the role i like the show itself goulet said it 
offers some poetry its a classroom in a sense to help people to 
lead saner and more honest lives 
jones hopes the tour results in a television film a 
videocassette and a new album the musical has not been recorded in 
english since the original offbroadway cast recording and a tv 
adaptation starring ricardo montalban as el gallo and john davidson 
as the boy has not been shown since its 1964 telecast 
people are going to rediscover the fantasticks and though 
they may have liked it before i think therell be a whole new 
vision of it he said 
