thought it would be appropriate to propose our own ideas 
ishihara said 
they suggested that the united states spend 5 percent of its 
gross national product on education adopt management styles 
prevalent in japan establish taxfree savings accounts and enact 
harsher punishments for criminals 
ishihara has been raising eyebrows since 1956 when at age 24 he 
published his first bestseller a novel called season of the 
sun the story of a group of affluent pleasureseeking youths 
who reject the abashed gloomy postwar mentality of their elders 
won the akutagawa prize japans top literary award 
a familiar figure on japanese television he is viewed by some 
as a possible contender for prime minister but his outspoken views 
have left him well outside the conformist political mainstream 
among the informed japanese public the overwhelming opinion 
is that mr ishihara is a troublemaker says tokyo university 
professor seizaburo sato if tokyo were to sever its security 
ties with washington it would automatically be cut off from the 
western camp regardless of how much of an economic foothold it 
might have gained in western countries said yoshihisa komori 
