the ps1 ibms major fullsized personal computer line is the 
ps2 may have some of the same drawbacks as the pcjr 
for example the new home pcs are said to lack socalled 
expansion slots that would allow customers to increase the 
machines memory or hook them to a computer network in addition 
the keyboards will not be fullsized analysts say though they 
will be more acceptable than the rubberized chiclet keyboards 
that helped do in the pcjr 
some analysts say those design limitations were intentional to 
avoid cannibalizing sales of ibms higherpriced pcs that could be 
a major issue with the specialized computer stores that sell ibms 
conventional computers martin said 
